wiki.content: “Lean Wit Me” is Juice WRLD’s third official single, following “All Girls Are The Same” and “Lucid Dreams.” Similar to the previously mentioned songs, “Lean Wit Me” is produced by Nick Mira. The song was released on May 22, 2018. The song itself revolves around Juice WRLD’s self-admitted struggle with his (ab)use of drugs and the consequences they’re having on his life. Although he knows the substances really harm him, he cannot seem to quit and give up on getting high. Unlike the previous two singles, “Lean Wit Me” was released on streaming services on the same date as its release, being his first track to do so. The official music video for this track released on August 2, 2018. The video featured Juice at an Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) meeting, an organization whose goal is to “stay sober and help other alcoholics achieve sobriety.” The AA setting is also similar to Eminem’s “When I’m Gone” music video.
